<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,625,330,357]" box="[151,625,330,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,625,330,357]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,625,330,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Family 
<taxonomicName authority="Ehrenberg, 1834" authorityName="Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1834" box="[245,625,330,357]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Antipathidae Ehrenberg, 1834</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,403,1005]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
This family was the first to be established and contains the highest number of species, with around 130 descriptions (
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko, D. M." box="[221,384,439,465]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="950 - 1017" refId="ref37985" refString="Opresko, D. M. (1972) Redescriptions and reevaluations of the antipatharians described by L. F. de Pourtales. Bulletin of Marine Science, 22, 950 - 1017." type="journal article" year="1972">Opresko 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko, D. M." box="[395,454,439,465]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref38020" refString="Opresko, D. M. (1974) A study of the classification of the Antipatharia (Coelenterata: Anthozoa) with redescriptions of eleven species. Ph. D. Dissertation, University of Miami, Miami, 193 pp." type="book" year="1974">1974</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Molodtsova, T. &amp; Opresko, D." box="[466,800,439,465]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref37781" refString="Molodtsova, T. &amp; Opresko, D. (2020) World List of Antipatharia. Antipatharia. Accessed through: World Register of Marine Species. Available from: http: // www. marinespecies. org / aphia. php? p = taxdetails &amp; id = 22549 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Molodtsova &amp; Opresko 2020</bibRefCitation>
). The family is characterized by unbranched species that have a single stem, and branched forms that can be bushy, arborescent, fan-shaped or bramble-like. Clearly defined pinnules are never present, but flabellate species can appear pinnulate because of the bilateral arrangement of the smallest terminal branches. The spines are smooth or papillose and can be simple, forked or multi-lobed. The polyps have ten mesenteries and range from 
<quantity box="[561,672,583,609]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1 to 3 mm</quantity>
in size (
<bibRefCitation author="Brugler, M. R. &amp; Opresko, D. M. &amp; France, S. C." box="[761,975,583,609]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="312 - 361" refId="ref36269" refString="Brugler, M. R., Opresko, D. M. &amp; France, S. C. (2013) The evolutionary history of the order Antipatharia (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Hexacorallia) as inferred from mitochondrial and nuclear DNA: implications for black coral taxonomy and systematics. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 169 (2), 312 - 361. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12060" type="journal article" year="2013">
Brugler 
<emphasis box="[854,909,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). Polyps are not elongate in the transverse plane and sagittal tentacles are generally longer than the lateral tentacles (
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko, D. M. &amp; Sanchez, J. A." box="[976,1139,618,645]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="492 - 507" refId="ref38515" refString="Opresko, D. M. &amp; Sanchez, J. A. (2005) Caribbean shallow-water black corals (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Antipatharia). Caribbean Journal of Science, 41 (3), 492 - 507." type="journal article" year="2005">Opresko 2005</bibRefCitation>
b; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wagner, D." box="[1164,1330,618,645]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="24" refId="ref39560" refString="Wagner, D. (2015 a) A taxonomic survey of the shallow-water (&lt;150 m) black corals (Cnidaria: Antipatharia) of the Hawaiian Islands. Frontiers in Marine Science, 2, 24. https: // doi. org / 10.3389 / fmars. 2015.00024" type="journal article" year="2015">Wagner 2015a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,403,1005]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
There are currently nine genera within the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1834" box="[674,823,655,681]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Antipathidae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pallas" authorityYear="1766" box="[834,954,655,681]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" genus="Antipathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[834,954,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Antipathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[967,1137,655,681]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" genus="Arachnopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[967,1137,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Arachnopathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="van Pesch" authorityYear="1914" box="[1150,1281,655,681]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" genus="Hillopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1150,1281,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Hillopathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brook" authorityYear="1889" box="[1295,1429,655,681]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" genus="Pteropathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1295,1429,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pteropathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brook" authorityYear="1889" box="[151,294,691,717]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" genus="Stichopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,294,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Stichopathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Blainville" authorityYear="1834" box="[308,451,691,717]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" genus="Cirrhipathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[308,451,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Cirrhipathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[464,683,691,717]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" genus="Pseudocirrhipathes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[464,683,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pseudocirrhipathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Opresko &amp; Cairns" authorityYear="1994" box="[696,816,691,717]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" genus="Allopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[696,816,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Allopathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Horowitz, 2020" authorityYear="2020" box="[869,1014,691,717]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" genus="Blastopathes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[869,1014,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Blastopathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Members of this family typically occur at depths less than 
<quantity box="[407,481,727,753]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="m" value="200.0">200 m</quantity>
, but some species may occur deeper (
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko, D. M." box="[905,1070,727,753]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="149 - 186" refId="ref38416" refString="Opresko, D. M. (2019) New species of black corals (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Antipatharia) from the New Zealand region, part 2. New Zealand Journal of Zoology, 47 (3), 149 - 186. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03014223.2019.1650783" type="journal article" year="2019">Opresko 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Revisions have been published to clarify the taxonomic position of many antipatharian families (Opresko 2001, 2002, 2003b, 2004, 2005a, 2006), but the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1834" box="[314,459,799,825]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Antipathidae</taxonomicName>
still needs a major revision since colony and skeleton morphologies are very heterogeneous, and genomic studies have identified a number of polyphyletic groups (
<bibRefCitation author="Bo, M. &amp; Bavestrello, G. &amp; Barucca, M. &amp; Makapedua, D. M. &amp; Poliseno, A. &amp; Forconi, M. &amp; Olmo, E. &amp; Canapa, A." box="[1017,1198,835,861]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref35820" refString="Bo, M., Bavestrello, G., Barucca, M., Makapedua, D. M., Poliseno, A., Forconi, M., Olmo, E. &amp; Canapa, A. (2012 a) Morphological and molecular characterization of the problematic whip black coral genus Stichopathes (Hexacorallia: Antipatharia) from Indonesia (North Sulawesi, Celebes Sea). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 166, 1 - 13. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2012.00834. x" type="journal article" year="2012">
Bo 
<emphasis box="[1058,1114,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
2012 a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Brugler, M. R. &amp; Opresko, D. M. &amp; France, S. C." box="[1209,1425,835,861]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="312 - 361" refId="ref36269" refString="Brugler, M. R., Opresko, D. M. &amp; France, S. C. (2013) The evolutionary history of the order Antipatharia (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Hexacorallia) as inferred from mitochondrial and nuclear DNA: implications for black coral taxonomy and systematics. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 169 (2), 312 - 361. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12060" type="journal article" year="2013">
Brugler 
<emphasis box="[1302,1358,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). For example, the 
<typeStatus box="[344,392,871,897]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pallas" authorityYear="1766" box="[627,747,871,897]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" genus="Antipathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[627,747,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Antipathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Pallas, 1766" authorityName="Pallas" authorityYear="1766" box="[759,1148,871,897]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" genus="Antipathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="dichotoma">
<emphasis box="[759,1003,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Antipathes dichotoma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pallas, P. S." box="[1010,1148,871,897]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref38623" refString="Pallas, P. S. (1766) Elenchus Zoophytorum Sistens Generum Adumbrationes Generaliores et Specierum Cognitarum Succinctas Descriptiones Cum Selectis Auctorum Synonymis. Hagae-Comitum, Frankfurt, 451 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 6595" type="book" year="1766">Pallas, 1766</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is more closely related to members of the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Opresko" authorityYear="2004" box="[411,588,907,933]" class="Anthozoa" family="Aphanipathidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Aphanipathidae</taxonomicName>
than to many members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1834" box="[888,1036,907,933]" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Antipathidae</taxonomicName>
. Future studies gathering molecular and morphological data from large sets of widely distributed specimens will be needed to reassess the current classification of both families (
<bibRefCitation author="Brugler, M. R. &amp; Opresko, D. M. &amp; France, S. C." box="[454,673,979,1005]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="312 - 361" refId="ref36269" refString="Brugler, M. R., Opresko, D. M. &amp; France, S. C. (2013) The evolutionary history of the order Antipatharia (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Hexacorallia) as inferred from mitochondrial and nuclear DNA: implications for black coral taxonomy and systematics. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 169 (2), 312 - 361. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12060" type="journal article" year="2013">
Brugler 
<emphasis box="[549,605,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
